            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At its meeting on May 5, 1949, the National Security Council considered a draft
                    report on proposed measures to achieve an agreed minimum list of goods not to be
                    included in exports from Western European countries to Eastern Europe. The
                    Council reached no decision, and action on the draft report, which had been
                    proposed by the Department of State and designated <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 46, was deferred.</p>
                <p>The text of the draft report was not declassified in time to be included in this
                    volume of documents.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
